                <note rend="inline" type="source">463.00 R 29/118: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-23T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Logan’s B–732, August 7, 4 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d364fn8">Transmitted in
                        telegram from the Chargé in France, no. 311, Aug. 7, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Inform Austrian Government that this Government has noted the action taken by the
                    Reparations Commission on August 7, and is prepared, within limits of Public
                    Resolution number 46, April 6, last,<note n="9" xml:id="d364fn9">Text quoted in
                        note of Apr. 13, to the Austrian Chargé, <ref target="#pg_617">p.
                        617</ref>.</note> to suspend priorities to the extent necessary for
                    realization of new Austrian Bank of Issue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
